---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '../../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
import Icon from '../../components/Icon.astro';
import FinalCta from '../../components/FinalCta.astro';
import { postBySlug } from '../../data/posts';
import { site, waLink } from '../../data/site';

const post = postBySlug('cheap-iptv-uk-scam-or-legit')!;
const canonical = `${site.url}/blog/${post.slug}/`;
const ogImage = post.image.startsWith('http') ? post.image : site.url + post.image;

const redFlags = [
  {
    title: '"Lifetime IPTV" for under £50',
    detail:
      'Running a real IPTV service costs money every single month: bandwidth, server capacity, transcoding infrastructure, EPG data feeds. No provider can sustain that indefinitely for a one-off payment of £30. When sellers use "lifetime" they mean "until the server gets shut down or we decide to stop," usually within 30 to 90 days of your payment.',
  },
  {
    title: 'Payment only accepted in crypto or gift cards',
    detail:
      'Card and PayPal payments come with chargeback protection. Crypto and gift cards come with none. Sellers who push you toward untraceable payment methods are insulating themselves from refund requests. That tells you everything about their confidence in their own product.',
  },
  {
    title: 'No website, only a Telegram username and a WhatsApp number',
    detail:
      'A real UK IPTV provider has a website, terms of service, a privacy policy and a documented refund window. A Telegram handle is not a business. It\'s a person who can disappear before your first month is up.',
  },
  {
    title: '"50,000 channels" and "all sports packages" for £2.99 a month',
    detail:
      'The channel count doesn\'t add up. Legitimate providers serve 8,000 to 15,000 channels because that covers the realistic catalogue of streams worth watching. Listings that advertise 50,000 channels are counting duplicates, broken streams and test feeds. The maths on £2.99 for licensed content doesn\'t work either.',
  },
  {
    title: 'No trial and no refund policy stated anywhere',
    detail:
      'Any provider that asks for 12 months\' money up front with zero trial period and no documented refund process is telling you they won\'t stand behind their service. A confident provider offers a trial. Full stop.',
  },
  {
    title: 'You get a new server URL every week or two',
    detail:
      'If your app breaks regularly and the seller\'s fix is always "use this new link instead", you\'re on a nomadic reseller line that keeps getting taken down. That is not a service. It\'s a permanent chase that ends when the seller stops responding.',
  },
  {
    title: 'Testimonials that reverse-image-search to stock photo sites',
    detail:
      'Open Google Images and drag a testimonial photo from any suspicious IPTV site into the search bar. Stock photos and recycled reviews are near-universal among scam operations. A real provider has real customers who agreed to be quoted.',
  },
  {
    title: 'No UK-reachable contact method',
    detail:
      'Even an overseas provider targeting UK viewers should have a responsive email or WhatsApp channel. A contact form that generates no reply is a scam signal, not a staffing issue.',
  },
];

const valueSignals = [
  'A documented refund policy linked in the footer, not buried three clicks deep',
  'WhatsApp support with real response times during UK business hours',
  'Card and PayPal accepted as standard payment options',
  'A structured trial period of at least 24 hours, ideally 30 days',
  'Realistic pricing between £8 and £15 per month when billed annually',
  'Terms of service and privacy policy published on the site',
  'A single, stable server URL that doesn\'t change week to week',
  'Honest channel count, not inflated with dead streams',
];

const faqs = [
  {
    q: 'Is cheap IPTV in the UK always a scam?',
    a: `Not always, but "cheap" in the UK IPTV market has a real floor. Anything under £5 per month for a full-featured service almost certainly runs on unlicensed infrastructure. A properly operated UK IPTV provider costs £8 to £15 per month at annual pricing: that's what server costs, EPG licences and support actually require. Our UK IPTV BOX 1-month plan at £${site.price} sits at the honest entry point of that range, so you can verify the service without committing to a year.`,
  },
  {
    q: 'What is the cheapest safe way to test an IPTV service?',
    a: `Take a 1-month plan from a provider with a documented refund policy and direct WhatsApp support. Our UK IPTV BOX subscription is £${site.price} for the full 30 days on the same servers our annual customers use. That's the lowest-risk way to properly test an iptv subscription uk without handing money to someone who might disappear.`,
  },
  {
    q: 'I paid a Facebook seller and my IPTV stopped working: can I get my money back?',
    a: 'If you paid by card, contact your card issuer the same day and open a chargeback dispute. If you paid via PayPal Goods and Services, open a dispute through the PayPal resolution centre. Crypto and gift card payments have no recovery mechanism. The gov.uk consumer protection pages cover the chargeback process in detail.',
  },
  {
    q: 'What is the difference between "cheap" and "affordable" IPTV?',
    a: 'Affordable UK IPTV is £8 to £15 per month for a service with stable servers, a real EPG and someone to answer your messages. Cheap IPTV is a £3 "lifetime" link from a Telegram account. Same word, different products entirely: one is a smart purchase, the other is a bet on a stranger not disappearing.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Why does your trial cost £14.99 instead of being free?',
    a: 'Running an IPTV server for 30 days costs real money. Bandwidth, transcoding, EPG data and support time all have a price per user per month. Charging £14.99 for the UK IPTV BOX 1-month plan filters out abuse and lets us hand you the exact same infrastructure our annual customers use, not a stripped-down demo. It\'s the honest cost of a proper first month.',
  },
  {
    q: 'How do I report an IPTV scam in the UK?',
    a: 'Report the seller to Action Fraud via actionfraud.police.uk. Contact your bank the same day if you paid by card. If the seller\'s site is UK-hosted, a takedown request via Nominet or the hosting provider is possible for repeat offenders.',
  },
];

const jsonLd = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@graph': [
    {
      '@type': 'BreadcrumbList',
      itemListElement: [
        { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 1, name: 'Home', item: `${site.url}/` },
        { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 2, name: 'Blog', item: `${site.url}/blog/` },
        { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 3, name: post.title, item: canonical },
      ],
    },
    {
      '@type': 'Article',
      headline: post.title,
      description: post.excerpt,
      image: ogImage,
      author: { '@type': 'Person', name: post.author, url: `${site.url}/about#team` },
      publisher: {
        '@type': 'Organization',
        name: site.name,
        url: site.url,
        logo: { '@type': 'ImageObject', url: `${site.url}/og-image.svg` },
      },
      datePublished: post.published,
      dateModified: post.updated,
      mainEntityOfPage: canonical,
      articleSection: 'IPTV Buying Guides',
      keywords: post.keywords.join(', '),
    },
    {
      '@type': 'FAQPage',
      mainEntity: faqs.map((f) => ({
        '@type': 'Question',
        name: f.q,
        acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: f.a },
      })),
    },
  ],
};

const relatedLinks = [
  { href: '/blog/iptv-subscription-uk-buyers-guide/', label: "IPTV Subscription UK: 2026 Buyer's Guide" },
  { href: '/blog/iptv-free-trial-uk/', label: 'IPTV Free Trial UK: What a Legit Test Looks Like' },
  { href: '/blog/is-iptv-legal-uk/', label: 'Is IPTV Legal in the UK? 2026 Explainer' },
  { href: '/blog/top-5-iptv-boxes-uk-2026/', label: 'Top 5 IPTV Boxes UK 2026: Ranked & Tested' },
];

const publishedFmt = new Date(post.published).toLocaleDateString('en-GB', {
  day: 'numeric', month: 'long', year: 'numeric',
});
const updatedFmt = new Date(post.updated).toLocaleDateString('en-GB', {
  day: 'numeric', month: 'long', year: 'numeric',
});
---
<BaseLayout
  title={`${post.title} | ${site.name}`}
  description={post.excerpt}
  canonical={canonical}
  ogImage={ogImage}
  includeSchema={false}
>
  <Header />
  <main id="main">
    <section class="relative overflow-hidden border-b border-border-subtle">
      <div class="pointer-events-none absolute inset-0 -z-10 opacity-70">
        <div class="absolute -top-40 left-1/2 h-[560px] w-[900px] -translate-x-1/2 rounded-full bg-grad-brand-soft blur-3xl"></div>
      </div>
      <div class="container-x pt-14 pb-12 md:pt-20 md:pb-16 max-w-3xl">
        <nav aria-label="Breadcrumb" class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-text-muted">
          <a href="/" class="hover:text-brand-light">Home</a>
          <span class="mx-2 text-border-subtle">/</span>
          <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-brand-light">Blog</a>
          <span class="mx-2 text-border-subtle">/</span>
          <span class="text-text-primary">Cheap IPTV UK</span>
        </nav>

        <div class="mt-6 flex flex-wrap items-center gap-3 text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-text-muted">
          <span class="eyebrow">{post.category}</span>
          <span>· {post.readMinutes} min read</span>
          <span>· By {post.author}</span>
        </div>

        <h1 class="mt-6 font-display text-3xl md:text-5xl font-bold tracking-tight text-text-primary">
          {post.title}
        </h1>
        <p class="mt-5 text-lg text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
          The UK's <strong>cheap IPTV</strong> market is a minefield. Genuine bargains exist. So do
          hundreds of "£3 a month for everything" scams that vanish two weeks after you pay. This
          guide teaches you to spot the difference, and how our
          <a href="/#pricing" class="text-brand-light underline underline-offset-4 decoration-brand/40 hover:decoration-brand-light">UK IPTV BOX 1-month UK IPTV subscription</a>
          is the safest cheap-entry route in 2026.
        </p>

        <p class="mt-6 inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-text-muted">
          <span class="h-1.5 w-1.5 rounded-full bg-brand-light"></span>
          Published {publishedFmt} · Updated {updatedFmt}
        </p>

        <div class="mt-8 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
          <a href={waLink(`Hi, I read the cheap IPTV UK guide — I would like to get the UK IPTV BOX subscription.`)} class="btn-primary" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer">
            Get UK IPTV BOX Subscription
          </a>
          <a href="#red-flags" class="btn-secondary">See the 8 red flags</a>
        </div>

        <figure class="mt-10 overflow-hidden rounded-2xl border border-border-subtle bg-elevated/60">
          <img src={post.image} alt={post.imageAlt} width="1200" height="630" loading="eager" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" class="w-full h-auto" />
        </figure>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="container-x py-14 md:py-20 max-w-3xl is-visible" data-reveal="fade">
      <article class="legal-prose">
        <p>
          We hear the same story on WhatsApp every week. Someone paid a Facebook group seller £30 for
          a "lifetime" IPTV subscription, got a working link for about three weeks, and then nothing.
          The seller's gone. The channels are dead. The money is gone. This guide exists to make sure
          the next person reading it doesn't end up sending us that message.
        </p>

        <h2>Why legitimate UK IPTV has a price floor</h2>
        <p>
          Running a proper IPTV service costs money every month, per subscriber. The main costs:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Bandwidth and CDN egress:</strong> the single largest cost at any real scale.</li>
          <li><strong>Transcoding infrastructure:</strong> converting streams into multiple resolutions for different devices and connection speeds.</li>
          <li><strong>EPG data licences:</strong> accurate TV guide data is licensed per market, not free.</li>
          <li><strong>Content licensing:</strong> the biggest cost of all, and the one every scam operator simply skips.</li>
          <li><strong>Support:</strong> real humans answering messages during UK evening hours.</li>
          <li><strong>Payment processing:</strong> 2 to 4% on every transaction.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Add it up and the minimum viable price for a legal, sustainable UK IPTV subscription sits
          around £8 to £10 per month at annual billing. Anything meaningfully below that is either
          skipping licensing (illegal), overselling server capacity (unreliable), or a straight scam.
          That's not opinion. That's <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/IPTV" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow">how IPTV economics work</a>.
        </p>

        <h2 id="red-flags">The 8 red flags of a cheap IPTV scam</h2>
        <p>Two or more of these on the same listing? Close the tab.</p>
      </article>

      <ol class="mt-8 space-y-4">
        {redFlags.map((r, i) => (
          <li class="card p-5 md:p-6 border-red-500/20">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
              <span class="flex h-10 w-10 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-red-500/20 text-sm font-bold text-red-300">
                {i + 1}
              </span>
              <div>
                <h3 class="font-display text-lg md:text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary">{r.title}</h3>
                <p class="mt-2 text-text-muted leading-relaxed">{r.detail}</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </li>
        ))}
      </ol>

      <article class="legal-prose mt-14">
        <h2>The 8 value signals of a legitimate cheap IPTV provider</h2>
        <p>
          Flip the red flags and you get the checklist for a provider worth paying:
        </p>
        <ul>
          {valueSignals.map((s) => <li>{s}</li>)}
        </ul>

        <h2>How UK IPTV BOX fits the "safe affordable" definition</h2>
        <p>
          We built our <a href="/#pricing">UK IPTV BOX subscription</a> to hit every value signal
          above and none of the red flags:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Not free, because "free" is where the scams operate. £{site.price} covers the real cost of running a proper 30-day test.</li>
          <li>The same servers our annual customers use, not a stripped-down demo line.</li>
          <li>Card, PayPal or bank transfer. Never crypto-only.</li>
          <li>WhatsApp support on {site.whatsapp} with genuine reply times during UK hours.</li>
          <li>Documented <a href="/refund/">refund policy</a> and <a href="/terms/">terms of service</a> published on-site.</li>
          <li>Realistic annual pricing available on request via WhatsApp. No "lifetime" promises.</li>
          <li>Real 4K, full EPG, catch-up on major channels, multi-thousand VOD library.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          If a previous scam has put you off UK IPTV entirely, the UK IPTV BOX 1-month plan is designed
          to rebuild that trust before you commit to anything longer.
        </p>

        <h2>How to protect yourself when buying any IPTV subscription</h2>
        <p>
          Whichever provider you go with, these steps apply:
        </p>
        <ol>
          <li>
            Pay by card or PayPal Goods &amp; Services. Both trigger chargeback protection under
            <a href="https://www.gov.uk/consumer-protection-rights" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow">UK consumer protection law</a>.
          </li>
          <li>Never enter card details into a Telegram chat or Facebook DM.</li>
          <li>Screenshot the sales page and refund policy before you pay.</li>
          <li>
            If you're scammed, report it to
            <a href="https://www.actionfraud.police.uk/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow">Action Fraud</a> the same day.
          </li>
          <li>
            The <a href="https://www.ncsc.gov.uk/collection/top-tips-for-staying-secure-online" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow">National Cyber Security Centre</a> publishes solid general guidance on staying safe when buying online, worth a read.
          </li>
        </ol>

        <h2>What you should realistically expect to pay for UK IPTV</h2>
        <p>
          In 2026, the honest price range for a 30-day trial from a legitimate UK IPTV provider is
          £{site.price} to £18. A full 12-month plan runs £90 to £140 depending on the provider and
          the connection count. That range gets you 4K live channels, a real EPG, catch-up, VOD and
          multi-device access from a provider that will still be running a year from now.
        </p>
        <p>
          Paying less isn't a saving. It's a bet on the provider surviving. Paying more than £25 a
          month is almost always a reseller margin with no quality uplift to show for it.
        </p>

        <h2>Frequently asked questions</h2>
      </article>

      <div class="mt-8 space-y-3">
        {faqs.map((f) => (
          <details class="group rounded-2xl border border-border-subtle bg-elevated/60 p-5 md:p-6 open:border-brand/40">
            <summary class="flex cursor-pointer list-none items-start justify-between gap-4">
              <h3 class="text-base md:text-lg font-semibold text-text-primary">{f.q}</h3>
              <span class="mt-1 inline-flex h-6 w-6 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-full border border-border-subtle text-brand-light transition group-open:rotate-180">
                <Icon name="chevron-down" size={14} />
              </span>
            </summary>
            <p class="mt-3 text-text-muted leading-relaxed">{f.a}</p>
          </details>
        ))}
      </div>

      <article class="legal-prose mt-14">
        <h2>The verdict: is cheap IPTV worth the risk?</h2>
        <p>
          Ultra-cheap IPTV (under £5 a month, "lifetime" deals, Facebook resellers) is almost never
          worth the gamble. You either lose the service or lose the money, usually both. The right
          interpretation of "cheap IPTV UK" in 2026 is <em>affordable</em>: £{site.price} for a
          tested 30-day trial, then £8 to £11 per month equivalent on an annual plan.
        </p>
        <p>
          Skip the risk. <a href={waLink()} target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer">Get UK IPTV BOX on WhatsApp</a>
          and we'll have you live in 15 minutes on servers you can count on for the next twelve months.
        </p>
      </article>

      <aside class="mt-14">
        <h2 class="font-display text-xl md:text-2xl font-semibold text-text-primary">Related guides</h2>
        <ul class="mt-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-3">
          {relatedLinks.map((g) => (
            <li><a href={g.href} class="card group flex items-center justify-between gap-3 p-4 transition hover:border-brand/50"><span class="text-sm md:text-base font-medium text-text-primary group-hover:text-brand-light">{g.label}</span><span class="text-brand-light shrink-0"><Icon name="arrow" size={16} /></span></a></li>
          ))}
        </ul>
      </aside>
    </section>

    <FinalCta />
  </main>
  <Footer />

  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(jsonLd)} />
</BaseLayout>
